rd, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"英国英格兰奧可福爾奧可福德","Devon, England":"英国英格兰戴文","lifeSummary":"当Mary Terry于1297年出生在英国英格兰奧可福爾奧可福德时，她的父亲Edward Terry27岁，母亲Mrs. Terry28岁。她于1315年12月28日与William de Wykeham在英国英格兰戴文结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。她去世于1370年在她的家乡享年73岁。"},"hr":{"1297–1370":"1297.–1370.","1290–1360":"1290–1360.","1320–1360":"1320–1360.","1323–1355":"1323–1355.","1270–Male":"1270–preminuo","1270–Female":"1270–preminula","9 April 1323":"9. travnja 1323.","1323":"1323","1355":"1355.","28 Dec 1315":"28. prosinca 1315.","1320":"1320","1297":"1297.","1360":"1360.","1370":"1370.","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","London, London, England":"London, England","Kingsbridge, Devon, England":"Kingsbridge, Devon, England","London, England":"London, England","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1297–1370":"1297–1370","1290–1360":"1290–1360","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1323–1355":"1323–1355","1270–Male":"1270–Zesnulý","1270–Female":"1270–Zesnulá","9 April 1323":"9. dubna 1323","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","28 Dec 1315":"28. prosince 1315","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","London, London, England":"Londýn, Anglie","Kingsbridge, Devon, England":"Kingsbridge, Devon, Anglie","London, England":"Londýn, Anglie","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1297–1370":"1297–1370","1290–1360":"1290–1360","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1323–1355":"1323–1355","1270–Male":"1270–Afdød","1270–Female":"1270–Afdød","9 April 1323":"9. april 1323","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","28 Dec 1315":"28. december 1315","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","London, London, England":"London, England","Kingsbridge, Devon, England":"Kingsbridge, Devon, England","London, England":"London, England","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1297–1370":"1297–1370","1290–1360":"1290–1360","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1323–1355":"1323–1355","1270–Male":"1270–Overleden","1270–Female":"1270–Overleden","9 April 1323":"9 april 1323","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","28 Dec 1315":"28 december 1315","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","London, London, England":"London, England","Kingsbridge, Devon, England":"Kingsbridge, Devon, England","London, England":"London, England","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Devon, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1297–1370":"1297–1370","1290–1360":"1290–1360","1320–1360":"1320–1360","1323–1355":"1323–1355","1270–Male":"1270–Deceased","1270–Female":"1270–Deceased","9 April 1323":"9 April 1323","1323":"1323","1355":"1355","28 Dec 1315":"28 December 1315","1320":"1320","1297":"1297","1360":"1360","1370":"1370","1270":"1270","1290":"1290","London, London, England":"London, England","Kingsbridge, Devon, England":"Kingsbridge, Devon, England","London, England":"London, England","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Terry","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish: from the Norman personal name <i>T(h)erry</i> (Old French <i>Thierri</i>), a short form of <i>Theodoric</i>, which is composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>theud</i> ‘people, race’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful), rich’. <i>Theodoric</i> was the name of the Ostrogothic leader (<i>c.</i> 454–526) who invaded Italy in 488 and established his capital at Ravenna in 493. His name was sometimes taken as a derivative of Greek <i>Theodōros</i> (see   Theodore  ). An Anglo-Norman family of this name has been in County Cork, Ireland, since the 13th century.","Irish: sometimes an Anglicized (‘translated’) form of Gaelic <b>Mac Toirdhealbhaigh</b> (see   Turley  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Terris","meanings":["Scottish (Fife): habitational name from Tarras in Rafford (Morayshire).","Catalan and southern French (Pyrénées-Orientales): from a personal name derived from the ancient Germanic name <i>Theodoric</i> (see   Terry  ).","French (southern); Catalan (<b>Terrís</b>): topographic name derived from French <i>terre</i>, Catalan <i>terra</i> ‘ground, earth, land’."]},{"name":"Tarry","meanings":["English (Northamptonshire and Leicestershire; of Norman origin): variant of   Terry   1."]},{"name":"Tyrie","meanings":["Scottish (Angus and Glasgow): habitational name from Tyrie (Perthshire) or Tyrie (Aberdeenshire). The placenames are from Gaelic <i>tìr</i> ‘(arable) land’ + a placename forming suffix (perhaps) <i>–in</i>.","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Terry  ."]},{"name":"Theodore","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Serge, Henri, Pierre, Alide, Andre, Antoine, Benoit, Berthony, Chantal, Daphnee, Edouard, Guilene.","French and Mauritian (<b>Théodore</b>); West Indian (in Haiti, Martinique, and Guadeloupe <b>Théodore</b>); English and Welsh: from a personal name derived from Greek <i>Theodōros</i>, a compound of <i>theos</i> ‘God’ + <i>dōron</i> ‘gift’, which was relatively popular in the Middle Ages because of its auspicious meaning. The name was borne by several early Christian saints. There was considerable confusion with the ancient Germanic name <i>Theodoric</i> (see   Terry  ). In Wales, the personal name <i>Theodore</i> was also adopted as an approximation to the Welsh name <i>Tewdwr</i> (see   Tudor  ). In North America, this surname has absorbed various other European cognates and their derivatives, e.g. Greek   Theodorakis  , Macedonian <b>Todorovski</b>, and Serbian <b>Todorović</b> (see   Todorovic  )."]},{"name":"Thierry","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Leonce, Olivier, Alain, Armand, Fernand.","French: from the Old French personal name <i>Thierri</i>, a short form of ancient Germanic <i>Theodoric</i> (see   Terry  ), composed of the elements <i>theud</i> ‘people, race’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful), rich’. This surname is also found in Germany.","History: Francis-Jean Thierry from France married Frances Bowen Blake in Marietta, OH, in 1815. Joseph Thierry from Germany married Susanna Plabuet probably in Detroit, MI, in 1846. Louis Thierry from Mulhouse in Haut-Rhin married Amelia Appelt probably in Michigan <i>c.</i> 1863."]},{"name":"Thilges","meanings":["German: patronymic from <i>Tilge</i>, a pet form of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Theodoric</i> (see   Terry  )."]},{"name":"Tear","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>ter(e)</i> ‘of fine appearance or character’. The name may sometimes have been confused with   Terry  .","Possibly an altered form of German   Thier  .","Manx: variant of   Teare  ."]},{"name":"Tjarks","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Fritz, Hermann.","East Frisian and North German: patronymic from <i>Tjark</i>, a short form of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Theodoric</i> (see   Terry  ), composed of the elements <i>theud</i> ‘people, race’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful), rich’."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Terry was born in 1297, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Edward Terry, was 27 and her mother, Mrs. Terry, was 28. She married William de Wykeham on 28 December 1315, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1370, in her hometown, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1297–1370":"1297–1370"